title: 820-3115 no fan spin
message:
Have a 820-3115 that had liquid damage. Replaced u7000 and surrounding corroded components. After doing this I had a fan spin for a few minutes. Not sure what happened but when I plug it in now I hear a small clicking sound and the green light blinks rapidly but no fan spin.

I now only have 11.82V on PPBUS_G3H

title: 820-3115 no fan spin
message: PPBUS voltage without battery? Green light present? 3V3_S5 present?

title: 820-3115 no fan spin
message: PPBUS 11.82V without battery. Green light present but flickers everu other second . 3v3_s5 present 2.56V

title: 820-3115 no fan spin
message: 11.8 is no good must be 12.23 or 12.56. Check resistance between pins 17/18 27/28 on U7000, also check R7005.

title: 820-3115 no fan spin
message: That's diode mode we want resistance mode.

title: 820-3115 no fan spin
message: Those measurements don't make sense. .21 is 21 Ohm? Now I'm doubting that 11.8v too.
